--- This event is raised when the camera's position or rotation matrix is changed. It can be used to alter the camera's transformations by changing `cameraTransform` for the third-person camera or `armCameraTransform` for the first-person camera.
--- @class cameraControlEventData
--- @field claim boolean If set to `true`, any lower-priority event callbacks will be skipped. Returning `false` will set this to `true`.
--- @field animationController tes3playerAnimationController *Read-only*. Provides access to the player's animation controller.
--- @field armCameraTransform tes3transform The new arm camera transformation.
--- @field cameraTransform tes3transform The new camera transformation.
--- @field previousArmCameraTransform tes3transform *Read-only*. The arm camera transformation before any changes. Identical to `armCameraTransform` if the player teleported a significant distance.
--- @field previousCameraTransform tes3transform *Read-only*. The camera transformation before any changes. Identical to `cameraTransform` if the player teleported a significant distance.
